+(Claude GitHub settings / repo App permissions → Contents: write).
+
+---
+
+## TL;DR for the morning
+
+- ⛔ **Blocker:** couldn't push — read-only GitHub integration (see box above).
+  Work is committed locally + delivered as a bundle in chat.
+- ✅ **Discovered + fixed:** Wave 1 was committed but never live (written to
+  root `app.js`/`style.css` that `index.html` doesn't load). Promoted into the
+  loaded paths. Wave 1 is now genuinely in the code.
+- ✅ **Wave 2 done:** "Iron-Gall Codex" visual identity — manuscript palette,
+  warm dark ground, gold-leaf bridges (the signature element), parchment reading
+  panel, reduced ambient motion, collapsible header. Verified headlessly.
+- ⚠️ **Needs you:** `ROADMAP.md` isn't in the repo — please commit it. The
+  Wave-2 direction is a **provisional taste call** (see NOTES.md) — redirect if
+  you'd prefer Copperplate or Astrolabe.
+- ⏭️ **Wave 3:** see the Wave 3 section at the bottom for exactly what I did /
+  didn't touch and why.
+
+---
+
+## Verification method
+
+Static site, no build. I test headlessly with Playwright-core driving the
+pre-installed Chromium against `file://…/index.html`: it loads the page,
+captures JS/console errors, asserts the 8 domains / 45 fields / 211 topics /
+72 bridges render, drives zoom to field + topic levels, opens field/topic/edge
+panels, runs search, opens the bridge index, toggles the header, and screenshots
+each state. (Google Fonts is blocked in the sandbox, so screenshots use fallback
+fonts — layout/colour/motion are faithful, letterforms are not.) Harness lives
+in the scratchpad; not committed.
+
+---
+
+## Log
+
+### 1. Wave 1 promotion (commit `af65e2a`)
+`index.html` loads `js/app.js` + `css/style.css`; the "wave 1" commit had put
+its code in root `app.js` + `style.css`. Copied the real Wave-1 code into the
+loaded paths, deleted the orphaned root duplicates. 15/15 headless checks pass
+(nav, panels, search, bridge index+story, LOD across zoom, collision pass, no JS
+errors). Separate commit so it's trivial to revert if you intended otherwise.
+
+### 2. Wave 2 — Iron-Gall Codex (commit `wave 2: visual identity`)
+
+Provisional direction (see NOTES.md) — **redirect me freely in the morning.**
+Built so each piece is independent and revert is cheap: the visual work is one
+appended block at the bottom of `css/style.css` (delete it → back to neon), plus
+8 colour values in `data.js`, one button in `index.html`, one small IIFE in
+`js/app.js`. What shipped:
+
+- **Palette — 8 domains as manuscript pigments** (`data/data.js`): iron-gall
+  pewter (Foundations), vermilion/red-ochre (Algebra), lapis (Analysis),
+  verdigris/oxidised-copper (Geometry & Topology), orpiment gold (Number
+  Theory), Tyrian mulberry (Discrete), turnsole violet (Probability), celadon
+  (Order). Every orb/halo/ribbon/label recolours automatically from these.
+- **The ground:** cold blue-black radial → **warm bister/vellum** radial
+  (`#241a0f→#17120b→#0d0904`) — warmer *and* darker. Faint static paper-grain
+  overlay (SVG turbulence, ~5%, fixed to viewport) on the map.
+- **Signature element — gold-leaf bridges:** the ★ signature bridges are now a
+  static, matte **gilt line with a fine dark under-edge** (reads as inlaid,
+  hand-laid gold leaf) instead of neon energy flowing along a dash. The gold is
+  the illumination; the bridges are the project's whole argument.
+- **Reading panel → aged manuscript leaf:** parchment ground + subtle grain +
+  warm top vignette, **iron-gall ink text**, gilt rules, illuminated story
+  drop-cap. (Reuses the paper CSS already in the file, re-skinned for every
+  inner element so who/via/story/bridge-row all read on cream.)
+- **Reduced ambient motion:** killed starfield twinkle (now static foxing),
+  title shimmer (static gilt + ❦ fleuron), domain-ring spin, field-pulse
+  breathing, and the flowing bridge dash. Kept interaction transitions and the
+  one-time field entrance. Added a `prefers-reduced-motion` block that stills
+  even those.
+- **Collapsible header:** a gilt chevron toggle in the title row hides the
+  subtitle + legend and shrinks the title, reclaiming ~50px of map (measured
+  147→97px), smooth transition, choice persisted in `localStorage`.
+
+**Verified:** 17/17 headless checks pass (nav, zoom L0→L1→L2, field/topic/edge
+panels, search, bridge index+story, header collapse *and* re-expand, no JS/
+console errors). Screenshots reviewed at all four zoom levels + the panel.
+
+Deliberately **not** done (left as your calls): craquelure texture on the gold
+leaf (drop-shadow was enough and lower-risk); the Copperplate platemark frame
+and the Astrolabe reticle (those are the *other* two directions in NOTES.md —
+pick one and I'll switch); any change to the atoms pages (they're standalone and
+untouched).
+
+### 3. Wave 3 (content depth, Geometry & Topology) — deliberately NOT started
+
+I stopped here on purpose, and I want to be explicit about why rather than guess:
+
+- **The gate is missing.** You scoped Wave 3 to "*only the parts the roadmap
+  marks as safe/unambiguous.*" `ROADMAP.md` isn't in the repo (see top of file),
+  so I have no definition of which parts *you* consider safe. Inventing that
+  boundary is itself a guess.
+- **Nothing mechanical is left.** I checked: all **211/211** topics already
+  carry full definitions, and all **8** Geometry & Topology fields are complete
+  (`Classical & Non-Euclidean Geometry, Point-Set Topology, Algebraic Topology,
+  Differential Topology, Differential Geometry, Low-Dimensional Topology & Knots,
+  Algebraic Geometry, Fiber Bundles & Characteristic Classes`). There are **0**
+  stub strings to fill. So the safe, unambiguous "turn a stub into `{label,
+  def}`" work is *already done*.
+- **What's left is editorial.** Per the README, remaining Wave-3-ish depth means
+  new L4 "named-theorem" cards, new interactive atoms, MathJax, or richer prose
+  — all of which are mathematical/authorial **taste calls** in a domain you know
+  far better than I do. Your instruction was: if it's ambiguous or a judgment
+  call you'd want to make yourself, *don't guess*. So I didn't.
+- **Push is blocked anyway**, so speculative content couldn't ship tonight.
+
+**If you want me to proceed on Wave 3**, the fastest unblock is to commit
+`ROADMAP.md` (so I can see what's marked safe) and, ideally, grant write access.
+Point me at, say, "add L4 theorem cards for Differential Geometry per the
+roadmap" and I'll run with the parts you've marked safe.
